# Python Standards — Movie Finder Backend

## Toolchain

- Python 3.13, `uv` workspace rooted at `backend/`
- Linting: `ruff` (rules: E, F, I, N, UP, B, C4, SIM) — line length 100
- Types: `mypy --strict` — must pass on every PR
- Tests: `pytest --asyncio-mode=auto` — coverage must not regress
- Format on save: Ruff (configured in `.vscode/settings.json`)

## Hard rules

- No bare `except:` — always catch specific exception types
- No `os.getenv()` scattered in code — load env vars once in `config.py` via Pydantic `BaseSettings`
- No `print()` in production code — use structured logging
- No `type: ignore` without an inline comment explaining why
- No mutable default arguments — use `None` + `if x is None: x = []`
- No blocking I/O in an async context — async all the way
- Docstrings required on all public classes and functions (Google style)
- Import order: stdlib → third-party → local (ruff `I` rules enforce this)

## Backend design patterns — follow these, do not drift

| Pattern                  | Where                   | Rule                                                                          |
|--------------------------|-------------------------|-------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| **State machine**        | `chain/` (LangGraph)    | New behaviour = new node or edge — never branch inside an existing node       |
| **Strategy**             | Embedding/LLM providers | New provider = new class implementing the interface — no `if provider ==` branching |
| **Dependency injection** | `app/` routes           | `Depends()` for db pool, auth, config, graph — never instantiate inside handlers |
| **Repository**           | Database layer          | Data access in repository classes — no raw SQL in route handlers              |
| **Factory**              | `chain/graph.py`        | Node construction centralised in `graph.py` — nodes are pure functions        |
| **Adapter**              | `imdbapi/` client       | Client maps raw HTTP → internal domain types — callers never see raw responses |
| **Configuration object** | All submodules          | All env vars loaded once via `config.py` — never `os.getenv()` in business logic |

## Pre-commit (run inside Docker)

```bash
make pre-commit          # from backend/ — runs ruff, mypy, detect-secrets
```

Never `--no-verify`. Secrets false positive → `# pragma: allowlist secret` + `detect-secrets scan > .secrets.baseline`.

## Running quality checks

```bash
make lint         # ruff check
make format       # ruff format
make typecheck    # mypy --strict
make test         # pytest --asyncio-mode=auto
make test-coverage
```
